{
  "texts": [
    "We report the results (win+tie rates) of public LLMs in Table 6.",
    "We observe that with the same number of model parameters, medical LLMs outperform general LLMs in terms of faithfulness and generalizability, but underperform general LLMs in comprehensiveness and robustness.",
    "These results are consistent with those shown in Figure 2, which demonstrates the validity and appropriateness of our metric and benchmark.",
    "This paper introduces BenchHealth, a healthcare benchmark encompassing medical language reasoning, generation, and comprehension scenarios.",
    "It employs metrics that extend beyond mere accu-racy, aiming to evaluate the utility and reliability of LLMs for clinical applications."
  ]
}